Resolves: rhbz#1220775 - “dnf langavailable” lists “fil” as available but “dnf langavailable fil” then says it is not available
See: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1220775

Current CLDR has

.../cldr-svn/trunk/common/main
$ grep 'language.*fil'  so.xml
			<language type="fil" draft="unconfirmed">Tagalog</language>

Which is probably not right, Tagalog seems appropriate for "tl",
it is not nice if "fil" has exactly the same translation.
---
 data/languages.xml | 4 ++--
 test_cases.py      | 6 ++++++
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

